statement:
The following non-trivial result was proven by Brouwer [@brouwer_bib]
around 1910 [@hatcher_at].

[**Theorem (Invariance of dimension)**]{} Suppose $U$ and $V$ are open
subsets of ${\mathbb{R}}^n$ respectively ${\mathbb{R}}^m$. If $U$ and
$V$ are non-empty and homeomorphic, then $n=m$.

[9]{} The MacTutor History of Mathematics archive, A. Hatcher,
*Algebraic Topology*, Cambridge University Press, 2002. Also available .
